// output: ../_includes/landing-page.html
div
  h1 Scorpion.css

  header

  p.description {{site.description}}

  h1 Time till release

  section.counter
    span.day
    span.hour
    span.min
    span.sec
div
  section
    h1.tac Simpler, more semantic code
    p.second-description We believe that the best developers are the lazy developers. That's why we encourage simplicity in our components, so that you can write less, to achieve the same results. To make your components even simpler to write, we highly encourage the usage of the <a href="http://learnjade.com/">jade</a> templating language.
    .row
      .col#responsive
        img(src="/assets/img/responsive-logo.svg" alt="Responsive")
        hr
        h2 Fully responsive
        p Scorpion components scale flawlessly, so that they can be used on any size device, from a phone to a desktop !
        
      .col#preprocessor
        img.sass(src="/assets/img/logos/sass.svg" alt="Sass logo")
        hr
        h2 Sassy as can be
        p Scorpion is a css (and js) library, written entirely in <a href="http://sass-lang.com">Sass</a>. You can quickly get started with our precompiled css, or build upon the sass source code.

      .col#semantic
        img(src="/assets/img/semantic.svg" alt="Semantic")
        hr
        h2 Readable HTML
        p We made our framework as semantic as we could, to make the code you write more readable, and more pleasant to write.
div#signup    
  section#signup
    h2.tac Subscribe to our mailing list, to know what we're up to !
    {% include signup.html %}
div  
  section#customisability
    .row
      .col.al
        img(src="/assets/img/customize.svg", alt="Sliders")
        h2 Make Scorpion your own
        p With tons of 
          a(href="/theming") theming variables
          | , and loads of comonents, that you can chose to include (or not), you can customise Scorpion to fit your needs exactly. You can also download one of our pre-made 
          a(href="/themes") themes
          | .
      .col.small
        h3 Theming examples yet to come!
  
div#numbers    
  section#numbers
    //- h1.tac Scorpion.css in numbers
    .row
      .col
        img(src="/assets/img/themes.svg", alt="themes")
        h2 Dozens of 
          a(href="/templates") templates
          
        p Scorpion has loads of pre-made templates ready to be used, to get you up and running as quickly as possible
      .col
        img(src="/assets/img/downloads.svg", alt="downloads")
        h2 Thousands of downloads
        
        p Even though scorpion hasn't ben launched yet, we have over 1k 
          a(href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/scorpion.css") npm
          |  downloads! 
      .col
        img(src="/assets/img/puzzle.svg", alt="puzzle piece")
        h2 Tons of extra components
        
        p Scorpion has a large library of 
          a(href="/extentions") custom components 
